    = image_tag('fusion-tacos.png', class: 'fit')
    %cite.mid-gray.italic.block.py2 Illustration by <a href="https://twitter.com/LauRARbee">Laura Bohill</a>
  %p <strong>Taco Fun Fact:</strong> <em>In April 2010, Food & Wine magazine named Roy Choi, the chef of the original Kogi's (Korean BBQ Tacos), one of its annual "Best New Chefs". It was the first time a food truck chef had been nominated for the award.</em> - <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korean_taco">Wikipedia</a>
  %p <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2009/02/25/dining/25taco.html">Roy Choi</a> put it best, “We tried to marry two cultures,” Mr. Choi said, “with this crazy idea of putting Korean barbecue meat inside a tortilla. We have never tried to make it any more pretentious or different from that, and we wanted to be very simple but delicious.” Now we're just waiting on someone to try making a ramen taco.
