  %h3.h2 Homemade Indian tacos and Indian frybread
  %p Mixing it up today with deep-frying Indian style tacos. Do you <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/disney-one-direction-singing-a38J69A5TuX72/fullscreen">trust me</a>? It's time to <a href="http://giphy.com/gifs/dance-makeup-indonesia-Q1fBo1zYD1By8/fullscreen">get weird</a>.
  .fitvid <iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/cN7L1RlrHbs?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
  %p.italic.mid-gray Source: <a href="http://hilahcooking.com/indian-taco-recipe/">Hilah Cooking</a>
  %h4.h3 Ingredients
  %p Frybread
  %ul
    %li 2 cups all purpose flour
    %li 2 teaspoons baking powder
    %li ½ teaspoon salt
    %li ½ cup milk
    %li ½ cup water
    %li Additional ¼ cup flour for shaping
    %li 2 cups oil for frying
  %p Indian Tacos
  %ul
    %li 4 cooked frybreads
    %li Cooked pinto beans
    %li Taco meat*
    %li shredded cheese
    %li lettuce, tomato, onion
    %li hot sauce, pickled jalapenos
  %h4.h3 Directions
  %ol
    %li Whisk the flour, baking powder and salt together. Combine milk and water in a separate cup.
    %li Add wet ingredients to flour mixture and stir with a fork to mix well. You will have a soft dough.
    %li Flour your countertop well with the remaining ¼ cup flour and coat your hands, too.
    %li Shape the dough into a cylinder and cut into 4 pieces.
    %li Pat each piece out into a circle about ⅓" thick (1 cm) and 6" across.
    %li Heat the oil to 350 degrees F and fry breads one at a time, for about 2 minutes on each side.
    %li Drain upright.
    %li Serve topped with beans, meat, cheese, and vegetables of your choice.
  %blockquote.taco-quote
    %p “The ultimate goal of farming is not the growing of crops, but the cultivation and perfection of tacos.”
    %cite Masanobu Fukuoka
